# Task Manager Application

This is a Node.js-based Task Manager application that provides CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing tasks.


### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/singlamohit1/task-manager-backend
   cd task-manager-backend


### File Structure
- controllers/
  - taskController.js
  - taskMetricsController.js
- migrations/
  - ...
- models/
  - task.js
- routes/
  - taskRoutes.js
  - taskMetricsRoutes.js
- app.js
- package.json

controllers: Contains the controllers responsible for handling HTTP requests and responses.
migrations: Stores database migration files for creating and modifying database tables.
models: Defines Sequelize models for interacting with the database.
routes: Defines API routes and connects them to the corresponding controllers.
app.js: The entry point of the application that sets up the Express server.
package.json: Contains project dependencies and scripts.

###  API Endpoints
/api/tasks
POST: Create a new task.
PUT: Update an existing task.
GET: Retrieve all tasks.

/api/task-metrics
GET: Get task metrics based on status and timeline.


### Database
The application uses Sequelize as an ORM to interact with the database. You can find the database configuration in config/config.json.
(a free tier postgres database is setup on cloud)
